{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"320c2340-83e5-4f43-8534-2730023df624","content":"\n\n","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_0egoE1u9WoPuwf5jP3tXV5","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project files"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_sRdmiOUhEow0qPc9I3X1J0","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4dd7cd56109a41cda906ef9e51732b75/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-4dd7cd56109a41cda906ef9e51732b75/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"91d63345-bfc0-45b1-8719-3ed74b9ba55d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 and 4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code investigation task.\n\nI know the answer to this: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, the SDK used Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default, but still supported VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0+, support for the legacy VSTest integration was removed entirely. The test projects built with MSTest.Sdk 4.x no longer produce the VSTest adapter/hooks needed for `vstest.console` to discover tests.\n\n\nI should check their project configuration to see what version they're running and what their setup looks like, so I can give them more targeted advice on how to resolve this.","outputTokens":305},"id":"9da4499b-257b-4ccc-9f34-461ae71322ca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:28:58.682Z","parentId":"d293ed54-e7f8-49a5-a2ae-e5438e4bb752"}
