{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"74427430-9f7c-48da-aeaf-8aece296a1b4","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0 dropped VSTest support entirely.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK defaulted to Microsoft.Testing.Platform but still shipped the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` could discover tests. Starting with **4.0**, the legacy VSTest integration was removed — test binaries no longer contain the adapter hooks that `vstest.console` needs.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended) — it uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively:\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This pulls in the VSTest bridge adapter so `vstest.console` works again.\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward with 4.x.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"91d63345-bfc0-45b1-8719-3ed74b9ba55d","outputTokens":251},"id":"6d9e3139-6c35-4361-ab54-46d54392514a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:29:08.023Z","parentId":"453966e7-57f8-4ffe-afd3-da5d6b79b6d7"}
